es.utils.mapper.impl.element

Class ElementMapper<IN,GETTER_OUT,SETTER_IN,OUT>

  • java.lang.Object
    • es.utils.mapper.impl.element.ElementMapper<IN,GETTER_OUT,SETTER_IN,OUT>
  • Type Parameters:
    IN - the type of the origin object
    GETTER_OUT - the type of the field (of the origin object) to be mapped into the destination object
    SETTER_IN - the type of the field (of the destination object) mapped
    OUT - the type of the destination object

    public class ElementMapper<IN,GETTER_OUT,SETTER_IN,OUT>
extends Object
    This class contains the informations and the logic needed the execute the mapping of an single element:
    • a Getter: a function that take a IN type object
    • a Transformer: a function that maps the result of the getter into the correct type for the setter
    • a Setter: a operation that assign the result of the transformer to the destination object
    Author:
    eschoysman
    See Also:
    Getter, Setter
